channel.description: Hi. I got this 639 server. I open "Run" and I get this message. I have the right jre and Jdk but, wtf?:

item.title: ~~~639 Run Prob~~~
item.dc:creator: @austin_cadle austin cadle
item.description:
@austin_cadle wrote:

[quote=“Doggie Skill, post:8, topic:432409”][quote author=austin cadle link=topic=535120.msg3912338#msg3912338 date=1328878153]

@echo off title Eclipse 639 java -server -Xmx512m -cp bin;lib/* org.dementhium.RS2ServerBootstrap pause

try this

@echo off title Eclipse 639 "C:/Program Files/Java/whateveryourjdkversionisherenotjre/bin/java.exe" -server -Xmx512m -cp bin;lib/* org.dementhium.RS2ServerBootstrap pause
[/quote]

Still not working[/quote]
further explanation:

@echo off title Eclipse 639 "C:/Program Files/Java/whateveryourjdkversionisherenotjre/bin/java.exe" -server -Xmx512m -cp bin;lib/* org.dementhium.RS2ServerBootstrap pause

in the whateveryourjdkversionisherenotjre

you have to actually put what it is, say you have jdk 7 or w/e

then in the: whateveryourjdkversionisherenotjre place, put jdk1.7.0_#
the # is only needed if it’s jdk 7.1 or higher if its just jdk 7 then only have: jdk1.7.0

if that doesnt work then just have jdk1.7

if it’s jdk 6 then in the : whateveryourjdkversionisherenotjre put jdk1.6.0_##

being your jdk number of course

this should work, if it doesn’t you need to update your jdk
